name: Bangku Tapau
description: ‘Bangku Tapau’ is inspired by the ubiquitous plastic stools commonly found in hawker or mamak stalls. Durable, utilitarian and copied endlessly, it is a true testament of a great design. Designed as flatpack, easy to dismantle for transport with a shoulder strap and a neat slot for hanging your favourite iced teh tarik. This was the design render before its realisation as a physical object - 99% made out of recycled plastic, it was displayed at the National Art Gallery, Kuala Lumpur.
